-- Escada Sees Medium-Term Sales of 500 Million Euros, SZ Reports
-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 2012-07-04T23:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/escada-sees-medium-term-sales-of-500-million-euros-sz-reports.html
Escada, the Munich, Germany-based
fashion company, may achieve sales of 500 million euros ($627
million) in the medium term,  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported in a
preview of an article to appear today.  Turnover for the fiscal year 2012 is likely to increase 5
percent to 7 percent to about 320 million euros, the newspaper
reported, citing an interview with Bruno Saelzer, chief
executive officer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Kraus in London at 
 jkraus2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
